    "Can large language models (LLMs) accurately extract information on suicidality from electronic health records (EHR)?",
    "In this analysis of 100 psychiatric admission notes using Llama-2 models, the German fine-tuned model (Emgerman) demonstrated the highest accuracy (87.5%), sensitivity (83%) and specificity (91.8%) in identifying suicidality, indicating the models' effectiveness in on-site processing of clinical documentation for suicide risk detection.",
    "The study highlights the effectiveness of LLMs, particularly Llama-2, in accurately extracting the information on suicidality from psychiatric records, while preserving data privacy."
